<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_c17fcb31-c76d-4bcf-8cdb-b4084213e587" outputclass="ncc-clause" variation="TAS"><sptc>E4P1</sptc><title id="_0c6e93fd-b7cd-4b39-a9f3-b2911d9c83cc">Surface drainage systems</title><archive-num>2019: FP2.1</archive-num><subclause id="_1f8a1ff1-325a-4df2-8778-84d29ddf85a0" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_e2016993-f2f2-4c52-bfba-e6ca85a4ae5c">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>A surface drainage system must have capacity to transfer the volume of water anticipated in an <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4602_0.3.0.xml#_74a0923e-1a7a-4396-a7ae-50c537bdfe8d" id="_b1ef422d-6152-4343-9212-67ab26a5003d" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">annual exceedance probability</xref> rainfall event. </p></subclause><subclause id="_1de451d9-b5f1-465f-a8c4-4cd69120a498" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_033b22df-c774-4381-84d5-1f28d0a51966">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p>The <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/4602_0.3.0.xml#_74a0923e-1a7a-4396-a7ae-50c537bdfe8d" id="_5b6dc2e3-8092-4f27-a6ab-756cd2782f80" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">annual exceedance probability</xref> must be appropriate to the—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_bb1dfa9f-b631-4e87-aa5e-14bfdafe767f">importance of the building; and</li><li id="_c131ee7f-2eb3-4c12-8b59-1633efc27f53">severity of potential damage to property, <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1362_2.0.0.xml#_ba5bd5ee-ef5f-41be-b153-43835028cd86" id="_e0475e43-052f-4472-939e-8a7b2d2663f8" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">loss</xref> of <xref format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/1c3f2f74-4ee1-4cdd-b1b4-53c91069d002/1186_0.6.0.xml#_905252bf-2ff1-43f8-ae81-2949aa116fee" id="_e47d4326-cf85-4f7c-a46b-b7cfbd4c89e6" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">amenity</xref>, illness or injury that would result from the failure of the system.</li></ol></subclause></clause>